  "name": "Production-Readiness Team",
  "description": "A cross-functional team takes a task from request to release-ready. The Product Owner frames the problem + testable acceptance criteria; the Tech Lead facilitates a round-table where Architecture, the full-stack SDET (engineering), Security, Performance and QA each reason through it and debate to a consensus design; the SDET implements + tests it; then Security audits the code + threat-models it, QA actually runs the suite against the acceptance criteria, and Performance reviews hotspots — concrete findings feed back to the SDET in a bounded fix loop; the Tech Lead gates and the Product Owner confirms intent before it ships. No frontend/backend split — one full-stack SDET does engineering. Executed by the xFrontier graph compiler with real repo/file/test tools in a bound workspace.",
